 the government, so the Constitutional arguments have no bearing on it. &#10;I disagree with prayer in school, prayer in Congress, swearing in on Bibles, having &quot;In God we Trust&quot; on the money, saying &quot;under God&quot; in the pledge of allegiance (I disagree with the whole concept of the pledge of allegiance, but the &quot;under God&quot; part the most),and indeed any type of collusion between church and state. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="693" language="en" documentId="1873" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Senor Hoint" date="17th March 2011 12:01 PM" docType="forumpost" origUrl="http://www.volconvo.com/forums/showthread.php?t=34286&amp;page=2" topic="prayer-in-schools" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="1873" notes="" title="Prayer in Public Schools"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="104"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="105" end="244"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="245" end="371"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="51" sofa="1" begin="372" end="693"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43 47 51"/></xmi:XMI>